Partly cloudy and small ripples on the water.
Partly cloudy and there is lots of algae forming around the docks.
Mostly sunny- almost calm- and small ripple on the water.
High sun- algae blooms in gobs on bottom- some floating to surface
Almost calm- bright high sun- dry
High sun- small ripples- heavy boat traffic
Sunny- calm- heavy boat traffic past 2 days
Cloudy- 4 in. ripple- moderate boat traffic
Calm- hazy sun- algae gobs rising to surface
Partly cloudy- small ripples- heavy boat traffic
Sky 95% clear- mild W wind.  6.25" of rain from 08/14-9/15.
Light overcast- lt. SW wind- and the temperature is 45 degrees.  1.7" of rain from 9/16-10/12.
Partly cloudy- 80 F- heavy boat traffic- algae clumps in shallows
Sunny- light ripple- medium boat traffic
Hazy- 30% cloud cover- heavy boat traffic
Southwest wind 13 mph- slight algae bloom- hazy- 4.5" rain 7/18 - 8/16
Sunny- breezy- medium boat traffic- heat wave last week
Overcast- calm- 33 F- 1.9" rain 8/16 - 9/27.  Cold out here!
Northwest wind 15 mph- 40 F- overcast- .6" rain 9/27 - 10/14
Overcast with small ripple on lake.  No boat traffic.
Great day- small ripple- no boat traffic.
Sunny- bright- 65 F.  The rain gauge reading from 7/24-7/25 is 4.05 inches.
Hot and muggy- slight south breeze- heavy boat traffic.
Cloudy- slight breeze- air temp 55 F.  The rain gauge reading from 7/24-8/26 was 2.05 inches.
Warm and humid- 15-20 mph south winds- white caps- rough/medium boat traffic.
Sunny- calm- beautiful fall morning- air temp 50 F- algae bloom visible in water.  Rain gauge reading from 08/26-09/25 was 4.7 inches.
Bright sunny day- west breeze- trace of snow last night- last test for year.
Reading taken by Howard Unrath- Assumed 12:00 + 15th day
Beautiful- sunny day- tests taken after Tuesday's heavy rains + Wednesday was very windy with light rain.
Partly sunny- E breeze- average 7/3 boat traffic
Calm morning with fog lifting.  Overcast sky- warm- 70s- wind picked up to 2-3 mph out of southwest.
Sunny- 32 degrees- southerly winds at 2 mph.  Cold- wind died and gave us a fantastic fall colored day on the lake.
Used total length of rope on secchi reading!  ice out about 5 pm 4/2/94.  Partly cloudy-very breezy.  Took reading at edge of ice in my normal spot.
Sunny- clear- north wind at 3 mph- beautiful
Hot 80 degrees- mostly sunny- small ripple on water.
South wind about 5 mph- beautiful day- clear blue sky- warm - 79 degrees already
North wind about 2 mph- breeze- plant life is reaching to the surface.  Sunny- scattered cumulus clouds- beautiful day!
North strong wind- no boat traffic- partly cloudy.

Today the breeze is about 3-5 mph out of the west.  Yesterday was about 25 mph or over.  Gusts out of the south.  Today is 59 degrees and heavily overcast.  The tree colors are at peak to beautiful.  Feels damp and threatening rain.
Sunny- temp is 42 degrees- 5-10 mph- wind is out of northwest- beautiful spring day.
8'-63 degrees- 19'-50 degrees.  Sheet: water color clear/blue.  Public perception 1.  Water temp. 74 degrees-2'- 63 degrees-8'- 47 degrees 19'-35'.
Northeast slight breeze- 78 degrees- beautiful on the lake- hot- more algae than usual.
South wind-almost white caps not quite- heavy boat traffic.  Assumed sample time was noon.
Water itch is gone.  Water cooled down.
Wind is 1-2 mph out of east- clear sky- sunny and beautiful.
Overcast- raining for days- 4.8" rain 8/11/95- 2.4" rain 8/12/95.
Overcast- light sprinkle beginning- breeze from east about 1 mph.  We have been having severe thunderstorms and high humidity.
Clear sky- small amount of pollen.
Sunny 80 degrees- heavy labor day boat traffic- south breeze- lots of weeds floating on surface + lots of Eurasian milfoil.
Cloudy- wind is from the west- about 3 mph- cold- temp is 48 degrees.
Beautiful day!  sunny- partly cloudy- calm- 60 degrees.
Due to recent rains the swamps have been backing up into the lakes rather than out.  S. breeze @ 7 mph- rain coming.
Slight algae bloom- water 69 degrees- ice out 4/22/96.  Water level: 9" high
Calm- sunny- with a little "hazy dog days feel!"  beautiful- 70 degrees.
Sunny- ~ 70 degrees- beautiful fall day! cold water.
Sunny- calm. 1 fisherman "Muskie" on grass. no other activity.
Itch is terrible.  Sunny and 70 degrees- muggy.  Breeze is southerly at about 5 mph.
Heavy boat traffic- water itch very bad- S breeze.
Hazy sun- S breeze- 80 degrees. muggy- heavy boat traffic.
High noon- calm- bright sun- minor boat traffic.
Overcast- easterly wind at 3-5 mph.  68 degrees.
Calm and overcast.  50 degrees.  The 39 foot sample for chemistry contained sediment.
West breeze at 5-10 mph.  The temperature is 65 degrees and sunny.  A beautiful day.
Cloudy E wind at 6 mph 65 degrees.
55 degrees F- S wind about 1 mph.  Sunny.
Water samples sent to Steven's Point.
NE breeze 5 mph.  Sunny 60 F.  Beautiful.
West breeze around 1-2 mph.  Sunny 60 F.  Beautiful!
SE breeze 2-4 mph.  Sunny 70 F.  Beautiful!
Light E breeze 1 mph.  Cloudy with some misty rain.  63 F.
Sunny- clear- 40 degrees F- calm- beautiful.
Partly sunny- (morning rain)- westerly winds at 5-6 mph- and 68 degrees F.  Nice day.
Sunny- 2-5 mph southerly winds- and 80 degrees.
Partly cloudy- southerly winds at 8-10 mph- and 61 degrees. (new van dorn bottle).
Sunny- clear skies- the temperature is 46 degrees F- calm- and NW-NE swirling winds at 1 or 2 mph.
Clear- blue sky- calm- and the temperature is 68 degrees.
Cloudy- the temperature is 65 degrees- and east wind at 3-4 mph.
Early showers- cleared to partly cloudy/sunny- calm- the temperature is 73 degrees and rapidly raising to 80 degrees.
Northwest wind at 10 mph- the temperature is 34 degrees F- and partly cloudy.  Beautiful fall colors- but COLD!
72 F- hazy- parlty sunny. SW windat about 5 mph.
Air temp 66 degrees. Water temp 67 degrees
59 F- cloudy. South breeze about 8 mph
cloudy- overcast- calm- occasional mist- (van dorn tube broke)
PARTLY SUNNY- 58f- nw BREEZE- 4-5 MPH- (STARCH PROBLEMS)
clear blue- 60F- calm- beautiful and perfect for testing
57.5F- NE breeze- cloudy with little sun- gusty winds- nasty
clear blue skies- 42F wind 8-10 mph- SW
Sunny 54 F- about 4 knots westerly wind.
Sunny- 65 F- 3 mph SE wind.  Beautiful day.
Sunny with a few cumulus clouds.  Calm to light NW breeze.  (guests Courtney + Emily Miller)
Calm- cloudy with thick cumulus.  69 F.
10 mph southern winds.  Sunny.  71 F.  Increasing winds 20 mph.
Air 36 C- winds WSW 10 mph. Overcast.
Sunny.  About 73degrees F.  Slight Northern breeze.
overcast and quiet. 63degrees F- slight South/eastern breeze- increasing.  Two eaglets squaking for food + loon floating nearby.
65 degrees- overcast- calm.  Increasing amount of floating plants--released naturally or cut off by boats.
59 degreesF- sunny/clear sky- slight SE breeze.  Beautiful fall day.
Note:  my records lists my storet# as 593045 not #593043.  Please check this.

column1: Six days prior (Mon.) the lakes were treated for EWM.

column2: Sunny- zero clouds.  Westerly light breeze- slight swirling.  77 degrees F.
overcast.  calm.  71degrees F.  (calm period after two nights of storms and rain: 1.4 inches one night and   second)
Wind calmed down for early evening testing.
65 degrees F.  Partly cloudy.  light Westerly breeze
Sunny with waning quarter moon above.  Easterly breeze.  Heavy rain + sotrm prior night.
Sunny with light northerly breeze.  Beautiful day!
Clear blue sky and sunny.  Light easterly breeze.  68 degrees F.  Perfect:)
Zero clouds- sunny.  78 degrees F.  Light southeasterly breeze.
Strong wind gusts (with three anchors and still not holding well)  Cloudy.  Storms possible.
clear sunny day with a light Westerly breeze. 71 degrees F
Partly cloudy- 54 degrees F- calm to slight NW breeze.  Beautiful!

Overcast and hazy- 60 degrees F.- light NW breeze.  We lost---ONE zebra mussel was found in late August- 2008 and the species has rapidly grown.  The water clarity has increased as a result of their filtering invasion.
Complete overcast- NW light breeze. 64 degrees F-  Thunderstorm last night with.6 cm rain.
Clear- sunny. Temp. 70 degrees F.- Southern wind- steady (made job difficult- with two anchors).
Very light SE breeze- sunny (zero clouds)- 67 degrees F.  Beautiful day!
N breeze- partly sunny- 60 degrees F.  4.3 inches of rain THIS week
sunny- windy- 15-20mph. hard to hold spot
Very windy stopped taking readings at 30 ft
